            <title>[HBASE-3270] When we create the .version file, we should create it in a tmp location and then move it into place</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3270</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Todd suggests over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3258&quot; title=&quot;EOF when version file is empty&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that writing hbase.version, we should write it off in a /tmp location and then move it into place after writing it to protect against case where file writer crashes between creation and write.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
